{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "lxxe:lamentations.5",
    "translationId": "lxxe",
    "bookSlug": "lamentations",
    "chapterNumber": 5,
    "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5",
    "summary": "Source text for Lamentations 5 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.5.1",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:1",
      "text": "Remember, O Lord, what has happened to us: behold, and look on our reproach.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.5.2",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:2",
      "text": "Our inheritance has been turned away to aliens, our houses to strangers:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.5.3",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:3",
      "text": "we are become orphans, we have no father, our mothers are as widows.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.5.4",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:4",
      "text": "We have drunk our water for money; our wood is sold to us for a burden on our neck:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.5.5",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:5",
      "text": "we have been persecuted, we have laboured, we have had no rest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.5.6",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:6",
      "text": "Egypt gave the hand to us, Assur to their own satisfaction.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.5.7",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:7",
      "text": "Our fathers sinned, and are not: we have borne their iniquities.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.5.8",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:8",
      "text": "Servants have ruled over us: there is none to ransom us out of their hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.5.9",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:9",
      "text": "We shall bring in our bread with danger of our lives, because of the sword of the wilderness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.5.10",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:10",
      "text": "Our skin is blackened like an oven; they are convulsed, because of the storms of famine.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.5.11",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:11",
      "text": "They humbled the women in Sion, the virgins in the cities of Juda.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.5.12",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:12",
      "text": "Princes were hanged up by their hands: the elders were not honoured.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.5.13",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:13",
      "text": "The chosen men lifted up the voice in weeping, and the youths fainted under the wood.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.5.14",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:14",
      "text": "And the elders ceased from the gate, the chosen men ceased from their music.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.5.15",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:15",
      "text": "The joy of our heart has ceased; our dance is turned into mourning.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.5.16",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:16",
      "text": "The crown has fallen from our head: yea, woe to us! for we have sinned.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.5.17",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:17",
      "text": "For this has grief come; our heart is sorrowful: for this our eyes are darkened.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.5.18",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:18",
      "text": "Over the mountain of Sion, because it is made desolate, foxes have walked therein.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.5.19",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:19",
      "text": "But thou, O Lord, shalt dwell for ever; thy throne shall endure to generation and generation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.5.20",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:20",
      "text": "Wherefore wilt thou utterly forget us, and abandon us a long time?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.5.21",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:21",
      "text": "Turn us, O Lord, to thee, and we shall be turned; and renew our days as before.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:lamentations.5.22",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:22",
      "text": "For thou hast indeed rejected us; thou hast been very wroth against us.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
